column1:
For a cybersecurity threat intelligence report targeting enterprise SOC teams, provide a taxonomy of the top five most prevalent phishing attack vectors in Q1 2024, segmented by:
1. **Initial access method** (e.g., credential harvesting via O365 fake login pages, malicious PDF/ISO attachments exploiting CVE-2023-XXXX, or adversary-in-the-middle (AiTM) proxy phishing bypassing MFA);
2. **Targeted protocols** (SMTP, EWS, OAuth 2.0 token hijacking, or WebSocket-based C2);
